news.title: Hyderabad development body's lottery for Rajiv Swagruha flats on March 3
news.para: There are more than 1,000 flats including 3-BHK, 2-BHK and 1-BHK which were unsold in the previous bids. Officials said those who can pay the token advance of ₹3 lakh, ₹2 lakh and ₹1 lakh for 3-BHK, 2-BHK and 1-BHK flats before February 15 are eligible for the lottery.

news.title: Bhopal civic body's affordable housing units could be disposed off under PMAY
news.para: BMC will appoint RERA-approved marketing agency or personnel for sale of unsold units,” said BMC additional commissioner, Chandra Pratap Gohal.

news.title: Bombay HC rejects PIL against additional FSI given to Pila House redevelopment
news.para: The PIL claimed that then BMC chief Iqbal Chahal had in November 2020 and August 2021, “illegally’’ given the builder, Rubberwala Housing and Infrastructure over 20,000 sq ft more than permissible developable space for redevelopment of Pila House-platinum in the Grant Road area.

news.title: Wife co-owner? Pay tax on 50% property income
news.para: Ruling in the case of Shivani Madan (the taxpayer), the ITAT consequently upheld a taxation of Rs 9.8 lakh in her hands during the financial year 2014-15 (the year pertaining to the litigation).

news.title: Five months on, only 12% Gurugram societies opted for unified billing system
news.para: DHBVN rolled out the unified billing system in September last year after receiving repeated complaints from residents that bills raised by the builder or RWAs are not following the standard tariff of DHBVN, as a result of which they aren't able to get the benefit of differential slab tariff.

news.title: Buying land off Yamuna expressway? You'll have to pay more from April
news.para: While the rates in the group housing and residential plot categories have been increased by about 33%, it is around 40% over in the industrial, institutional and IT/ITES categories. Buying land in the commercial category will also be costlier by 30%.

news.title: Three bidders in close fight for Rajesh LifeSpaces' hotel business
news.para: The three bidders have offered different plans which will now be evaluated by Resurgent Resolution Professionals, the valuer appointed by banks. Depending on the valuer's report, lenders will put the best plan to vote based on the net present value.

news.title: Godrej Fund Management puts two assets on the block
news.para: These marquee properties include a total of 200,000 sq ft office space spread across three floors in commercial project Godrej BKC and an information technology park project G: Corp Tech Park in Thane's Ghodbunder Road area.

news.title: Adani Cement's ACC and Ambuja to resume Himachal Pradesh operations
news.para: All stakeholders have amicably resolved the issues on freight rates in the state of Himachal Pradesh, the company said, adding that ACC and Ambuja will resume operations on Tuesday at the Gagal and Darlaghat plants.

news.title: China launches pilot scheme to boost private investment in real estate
news.para: Investors in the scheme, predominantly institutional, should offer no less than 10 million yuan each to participate, the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) said.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers posts net loss of Rs 160.82 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Parsvnath Developers' consolidated total income stood at Rs 87.75 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 70.89 per cent from Rs 301.44 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maha RERA issues show-cause notices to 313 projects for shortcomings
news.para: The shortcomings include total expenditure claimed to be incurred by a developer not reflecting on the ground, it said, pointing out that there are situations where a developer has claimed 75 per cent of the budgeted expenditure is done while the project is only 50 per cent complete.

news.title: Nashik civic body aims to make C&D recycling plant operational in six months
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has finally identified a plot of land adjacent to the existing civic compost plant in Pathardi, on the outskirts of the city, for this purpose.

news.title: Cluster development policy remains on paper six years after Pune civic body's approval
news.para: The policy has been kept in abeyance though the state government has approved the development plan for civic areas, but. If approved, the cluster development policy would promote the redevelopment of old wadas and smaller properties in Peth areas.

news.title: Hand over five apartments, consumer panel asks developer in Nashik
news.para: The three-bench commission passed its judgement in which it has ordered the developer to construct the apartments with complete amenities as promised and hand them over the consumer after getting the fees required for installation of electrical meter and registration costs.
